## GAP 5: Missing Node Middleware Context Type in Go parity

The Go middleware uses `context.Context`. Rust has a placeholder `Context` type in middleware/node/mod.rs but it doesn't support the full context pattern.

### Go Code (`/tmp/tork-go/middleware/node/node.go`):
```go
type HandlerFunc func(context.Context, *tork.Node) error
```

### Rust Code (`/home/lewis/src/twerk/middleware/node/mod.rs` lines 14-19):
```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct Context {
    #[allow(dead_code)]
    values: Vec<(String, String)>,
}
```

### Issue:
The Rust `Context` is not actually used as a context pattern - it's just a placeholder. The `get` method always returns `None`. The Go `context.Context` supports cancellation, timeouts, values, etc.

### Expected Fix (Optional/Nice-to-have):
Enhance the Rust Context type to support basic key-value storage, or document why the Go-style context pattern wasn't adopted.

